        "user": "Here is the canonical definition of \"transformer (architecture)\": A transformer (in machine learning) is a neural network architecture introduced by Vaswani et al. 2017 whose layers are built from multi-head self-attention and position-wise feed-forward sublayers with residual connections and layer normalization, processing all positions in a sequence in parallel rather than recurrently. Acknowledge that you have read it.",
        "assistant": "Acknowledged. I have read the canonical definition you provided.\n\nThat is an excellent and precise summary of the architecture. It correctly highlights the essential technical components:\n\n*   **Multi-head self-attention** and **position-wise feed-forward sublayers** as the core building blocks.\n*   **Residual connections** and **layer normalization** as the critical \"glue\" that allows the model to be trained effectively at great depth.\n*   The fundamental shift from **recurrent** processing to **parallel** processing of the entire sequence.\n\nThis formal definition perfectly encapsulates the innovations from the \"Attention Is All You Need\" paper by Vaswani et al.",
